schools.name: Windsor Hill Arts Infused Elementary School

data.description: Welcome to 2212 Sawmill Trace. Located in Windsor Hill, a hidden gem of North Charleston, this beautiful 4 bedroom, 2.5 bath home awaits you.  Zoned for the highly sought Dorchester District 2 schools, residents here enjoy the convenience of having their elementary school IN the neighborhood.This home has no governing HOA, so you're welcome to bring home your boat, trailers, and commercial work vehicles. The home is already equipped with a drive gate to the backyard for your immediate storage needs. Living here can save you time in traffic as the home is located just a few miles from the Air Force Base, airport, interstate, Publix grocery,Fort Dorchester High School, and the new state of the art North Charleston Aquatic Center. The home is also just a quick 36 minute drive to the beach.   An additional bonus to its location is the private school, daycare, grocery store, restaurants, and newer gas station located right at the entrance of the neighborhood. There's even a nearby Marshalls HomeGoods, Ulta beauty, LIDL grocery, and multiple restaurants now open within a 5 minute drive. Talk about convenience!  Inside, the home boasts beautiful wood floors, a wood burning fireplace, and great natural light. Entertain with ease in the spacious kitchen complete with updated cabinetry, appliances, granite countertops, and a walk in pantry.   Upstairs you will find 4 generously sized bedrooms, one of which is an oversized FROG (finished room over garage). The FROG is great as a bedroom, game room, or craft room. In addition to the rooms closet, it also grants walk-in attic access with tons of storage space on each side of the room.     At the end of the hallway opposite the FROG sits the spacious owners suite. This suite offers a great walk-in closet as well as a large soaking tub and stand-alone shower.   Outback, you can enjoy sunsets on the screen porch while watching your littles or pets play in the large, fully fenced backyard. Mature trees towards the back of the property offer privacy as well as a home to endless serenading birds in the Spring & Summer.    This backyard is the perfect place to entertain as the screen porch connects to a large covered pergola & patio. Relax, entertain, and cook out regardless of the weather. Just under a quarter of an acre, there's tons of space to play.   Garage enthusiasts will enjoy this homes garage space as well as the built in shelving and work bench, which will convey with the home sale. And when it's time to cool off, you can step inside and enjoy the breeze of the new, 2021 HVAC system.  Homes in this neighborhood don't last long. We encourage you to book your showing today!
